description:
Job Description

• Manage the on-site team and develop protocol, practice align with policies to perform the security & service

• Partner with business units to identify security deficiencies, and develop customized policies and procedures to gain compliance with regulations

• Provide advice and counsel on complex physical security, internal fraud investigations, prevention, life safety risk, fire safety, crisis management, and emergency response issues

• Handle and manage securing classified and sensitive information from the work environment and assigned task

• Prepare and present collected data, information, report and documentation for the scope related, including invoice and accruals

• To conduct threat assessment to the business, event activity and site

• Maintains a positive, professional environment in full compliance with applicable laws, regulations, policies and procedures; ensures that security force understand and comply with applicable laws, regulations, policies and procedure

Requirement

• Degree holder in any discipline;

• A minimum 3 years of experience in a supervisory position in the corporate security industry;

• Strong sense of security awareness, tough and with good communication and interpersonal skill

• Good knowledge in health, safety and environment;

• Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese;

• Strong prioritizing abilities, analytical and problem-solving skills;

• Must be competent and literate with computers;

• Immediate available is a definite advantage

Responsibilities: 

Lead Customer Service team members to handle customer enquiries, complaints and any incidents occurred;
Monitor and ensure accurate quotation, service order, invoice to clients
Liaise with customers to understand their needs and make appropriate recommendations;
Conduct site surveys and design security systems based on users' requirements as well as company's quality standard;
Support the project team to achieve team goal; 
Ensure close co-ordination with our global offices to ensure satisfactory customers service;
Perform ad-hoc duties as assigned.



Requirements:

2 years of customer service or sales in the services industry is a must;
Good spoken and written in Chinese, English and Mandarin;
Good common sense, communication & presentation skills;
Well organization, customer-oriented, people and project management skills;
Candidate with security system experience is essential

Job Responsibilities


Provide security and driving services to the employer;
Handle any matters assigned by the employer.

Job Requirements


Have relevant experience in security services;
Have any professional security or close protection qualifications;
Holder of valid Security Personnel Permit;
Holder of driving license;
Strong sense of responsibility, honest and confidentiality.

We offer good career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send detailed resume with availability, current and expected salary by clicking "Apply". 

(Applications will be treated in strict confidence. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)
